{
  "stem": "15197.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this was very, very much for me to have the feeling that somebody loves you and cares for you and is part of you.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it was natural, this kind of relationship, at that time for young people, although danger was surrounding us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was-- this was the life, full of danger.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when I went to visit his parents it was times when I got-- the underground has sometimes-- --a small amount of money which came from-- from the-- from England, from the Polish government in exile.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had representatives Otto [POLISH] and [POLISH] and sometimes American labor unions and organizations, Jewish Labor Committee sent through illegal ways money to England and from there, Polish parachute, like [POLISH], which he now lives in Washington, DC, an older gentleman.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was a Polish officer in the Polish underground which used to parachute to Poland with all kinds of money for the Polish underground and bring a small amount also for the Jewish underground.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At that time, we had a number of Jews we knew hiding among Poles.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we used to pay the Poles a small amount of money to be able to-- the Jews to keep them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And such a small amount of money, I was the one very often going to the Polish places where Jews were hiding and bringing.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I went also to the place where my husband's parents were and the people there didn't know that I am Jewish.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They knew that I am in the Polish underground.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this was where I used to come.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And-- --I recall that Friday the mother used to have candles, lighted candles.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They-- religious little traditional things they use in the hiding to go on.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
